  <name>Markforge</name>

  <summary>A markdown editor that just works — with live preview, Mermaid, LaTeX, and GitHub alerts</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      Markforge is the markdown editor I built because everything else either did too much or too little.
      Clean interface, live preview with synced scrolling, and all the features you actually need without the bloat.
      Runs locally, keeps your files safe, and gets out of your way so you can focus on writing.
    </p>
    <p>What you get:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clean, distraction-free interface following GNOME HIG</li>
      <li>Formatting toolbar for quick edits without memorizing syntax</li>
      <li>File manager to keep your docs organized</li>
      <li>Search and replace that actually works</li>
      <li>Export to HTML, PDF, or images when you need to share</li>
      <li>Dark mode by default (light mode if that's your thing)</li>
      <li>Auto-save so you never lose work to random crashes</li>
      <li>GPU-accelerated rendering for buttery-smooth performance</li>
      <li>Synchronized scrolling between editor and preview</li>
      <li>File history and versioning to track changes</li>
      <li>Built-in support for tables, Mermaid diagrams, LaTeX math, and GitHub alert blocks</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Whether you're writing technical docs, maintaining READMEs, or just taking notes,
      Markforge gives you everything you need in a fast, reliable package. No accounts, no cloud sync you didn't ask for — just solid local editing.
    </p>
  </description>

